description:
Assist in developing and managing the wholesale business of the brand in Hong Kong, Macau, Southeast Asia as well as searching for opportunities in China.  Develop new accounts, sales channel and distribution networks.  Identify market segment opportunities and drive business performance.

 


Requirements :

University Graduate;
4-6 years relevant experience in prestigious consumer products;
Fluent in English and Chinese (including Mandarin);
Strong connection with relevant luxury products groups;
Relevant wholesale business network is essential;
Solid B2B sales experience is preferable;
Highly strategic mind-set, independent and self-motivated;
Excellent communication skills with all levels (including senior) of clients;
Strong business acumen and sense of accountability.



We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.  Please apply in strict confidence (quoting reference on the envelope) by sending personal resume together with current & expected salary and date available to : Assistant Group Personnel Manager, T.S.T. P.O. Box 98537, Kowloon or our e-mail address : career@ dickson.com.hk

* All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Job Descriptions:

Handle customers' enquiries, provide product information;
Follow customers' developments and provide advices;
Negotiate price with customers and follow up sales orders;
Arrange vendor/customer-visit and build up relationship;
Promote new products to vendors/customers;
Prepare sales reports, analysis and sales forecast;
Assist managers in various kinds of sales-related programs and meet sales targets;

Business trip to is required, especially China / other Asian countries;
Assist in ad hoc duties as assigned, i.e. market research, survey, etc.

Job Requirements:

Tertiary education or above with 1 - 2 years working experience in sales, manufacturing, garment or merchandising industry is preferred; knowledge in snap and button will be a plus; FRESH graduate will also be considered;
Good command of spoken and written English & Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin);
Well versed with PC applications like MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint & Chinese Word Processing, proficiency in Excel Function (i.e. v-lookup, pivot table) is preferable;
Customer-oriented, teamwork spirit and outgoing characters are preferred;
Candidates with less/more experience may be considered as Associate/Senior Sales & Marketing Executive respectively.

Benefits:

5-day work (staggered working hours)
Double pay
Discretionary bonus
Group medical
OT pay
Statutory Annual Leave with extra 7 days Company Annual Leave
Statutory Holiday and Other General Holiday
Other Special Leave i.e. Marriage Leave, etc.

We offer competitive remuneration and benefits, holidays, stable working environment to the right candidates. Interested parties please click "Apply Now" and send your full resume with expected salary in MS Word Format to us (Please quote Position Name & Reference No.)

